  "text": "In the current study, the average pvCO 2 was 45.4 mmHg. [CITATION_1] found an average pvCO 2 at 3 wk of age of 53.8 mmHg in a high-risk broiler line and an average pvCO 2 of 43.9 mmHg in a low-risk line. Interestingly, however, the pvO 2 was lower (44.6 mmHg for the high-risk line and 46.9 mmHg for the low-risk line) than in the current study (52.46 mmHg). However, it should be noted that [CITATION_2] used only male broilers, whereas in the current study, the average measurements were based on results from both males and females. In addition, the previous study compared ascites susceptibility between 2 genetically different stocks (high-and low-risk lines), whereas the current study investigated ascites susceptibility within one crossed line.",
